divertors.code.output_flag.documentation: Output flag : 0 means the run is successful, other values mean some difficulty has been encountered, the exact meaning is then code specific. Negative values mean the result shall not be used.

divertors.divertor[:].target[:].wetted_a.documentation: Wetted area of the target, defined by the SOL heat flux decay length (lambda_q) mapped to the target using flux expansion and spreading factor and the target toroidal circumference. In other words, this is the area getting heat flux from the maximum value down to one e-fold decay.
Index in the error_description list for "data"

divertors.ids_properties.documentation: Interface Data Structure properties. This element identifies the node above as an IDS

divertors.ids_properties.comment.documentation: Any comment describing the content of this IDS

divertors.ids_properties.creation_date.documentation: Date at which this data has been produced

divertors.ids_properties.homogeneous_tim.documentation: This node must be filled (with 0, 1, or 2) for the IDS to be valid. If 1, the time of this IDS is homogeneous, i.e. the time values for this IDS are stored in the time node just below the root of this IDS. If 0, the time values are stored in the various time fields at lower levels in the tree. In the case only constant or static nodes are filled within the IDS, homogeneous_time must be set to 2

divertors.ids_properties.occurrence.description: occurrence number [NOTE: this field only exists in OMAS and is not part of the ITER PDM]

divertors.ids_properties.provider.documentation: Name of the person in charge of producing this data

divertors.ids_properties.source.documentation: Source of the data (any comment describing the origin of the data : code, path to diagnostic signals, processing method, ...)

divertors.ids_properties.version_put.documentation: Version of the access layer package used to PUT this IDS

Programming language of the Access Layer high level API used to PUT this IDS

divertors.ids_properties.version_put.dat.documentation: Version of Data Dictionary used to PUT this IDS

divertors.poloidal_sol_current.documentation: Set of axisymmetric divertor tiles through which poloidal currents in SOL are measured using shunt resistances. Tiles are modelled as piecewise straight line segments in the poloidal plane.

divertors.poloidal_sol_current[:].identi.documentation: Alphanumeric identifier of the measured signal
